<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Dawdle</title>
    <!--Import google icon font-->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/materialize.min.css"  media="screen,projection"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <!--Let browser know website is optimized for mobile-->
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  </head>
  <body>
    <% if ( messages ) { %>
      <%for (var msg in messages){%>
        <div class="flash"><%= messages[msg] %></div>
      <%}%>
    <% } %>
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <div class="navbar-fixed">
        <nav class="mynavbar">
          <div class="nav-wrapper">
            <a href="#!" class="brand-logo">Dawdle</a>
            <ul class="right hide-on-med-and-down navele">
              <li><a href="/myprofile">Myprofile</a></li>
              <li><a href="/wlogout">Log out</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="col s12 m4">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-image">
              <img src="/images/riddles.jpg" height="300px">
              <span class="card-title">Riddles</span>
              <a class="btn-floating halfway-fab waves-effect waves-light red" href="/wriddles"><i class="material-icons">forward</i></a>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <p>A riddle is a statement or question or phrase having a double or veiled meaning, put forth as a puzzle to be solved.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col s12 m4">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-image">
              <img src="/images/stories.jpg" height="300px">
              <span class="card-title">Stories</span>
              <a class="btn-floating halfway-fab waves-effect waves-light red" href="/wstories"><i class="material-icons">forward</i></a>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <p>A story is a report of connected events, real or imaginary, presented in a sequence of written or spoken words, or still or moving images, or both.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col s12 m4">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-image">
              <img src="/images/qoutes.jpg" height="300px">
              <span class="card-title">Quotes</span>
              <a class="btn-floating halfway-fab waves-effect waves-light red" href="#"><i class="material-icons">forward</i></a>
            </div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <p>A quotation can also refer to the repeated use of units of any other form of expression, especially parts of artistic works: elements of a painting, scenes from a movie or sections from a musical composition.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <footer class="page-footer teal">
        <div class="footer-copyright">
          <div class="container">
            copyright &copy 2018 reserved
          </div>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>




    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-2.1.1.min.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/materialize.min.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
